President Cyril Ramaphosa has placed Health Minister Zweli Mhkize on special leave. The Presidency says Mkhize's leave will allow him to attend to the allegations around the Digital Vibes contract. #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has placed Health Minister Zweli Mhkize on special leave. Tourism Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane will serve as acting Health Minister. READ: Digital Vibes scandal | Zweli Mkhize apologises The Presidency says Mkhize's leave will allow him to attend to the allegations around the Digital Vibes contract. Mkhize apologised for the disruption caused by the scandal saying his intentions were not to dodge questions but to make sure that he cooperates fully with the Special Investigating Unit. He says the matter has tainted the work done to fight COVID-19.